{
  "templateName": "cutout-over-themed-bg",
  "description": "Transparent-PNG subject cutout composited over a full-bleed themed background image, with a banner-staircase headline block and Looth logo corner anchor. Originated as the ted_bergstrand_ai_web_design_A_tech_dark layout — approved by user as a successful one-off worth reusing.",
  "aspectRatio": "16x9",
  "canvasSize": { "w": 1280, "h": 720 },
  "useWhen": [
    "Episode has a strong CONCEPT theme (AI, cyber, sonic, metaverse) that wants a themed background rather than a literal location/workshop photo",
    "You have a clean cutout or stylized rendering of the guest (android-ified, holographic, line-art) that reads on top of busy imagery",
    "Show is name-first — the guest's identity sells the episode, not the product"
  ],
  "toReskin": [
    "Swap 'Matrix BG' image src to a different themed background (1920x1080 ideal). Keep it full-bleed at scale ~0.67 for a 1280x720 canvas.",
    "Swap 'Ted Android' src to the new episode's transparent-PNG subject. Position bottom-right of center; scale ~0.7 for a ~720px tall subject.",
    "Update the three banner text values: Name (guest), Topic (episode subject), Date.",
    "Theme color: headline text fill (#51a457 matrix-green here) should track the background theme per SKILL.md 'Theme color > brand color for headlines'. Brand gold stays on the logo + accents.",
    "Stroke color on Name banner text (#FE6B4F coral) should stay complementary to the theme fill, not match it."
  ],
  "notes": [
    "Banner hierarchy via VARIED TREATMENT, not just size: (1) Name — huge outlined-only text, no panel fill, stands on its own against the BG. (2) Topic — transparent polygon (opacity:0) with outlined text, keeps the staircase shape without adding a second solid panel. (3) Date — solid dark panel with sage stroke, most contained. Avoids the 'three stacked rectangles' look that reads as templated.",
    "The 'Rectangle' layer at y=640 (scaleX 6.42, fill #015214) is a full-width green strip behind the logo — visually ties the logo corner to the matrix theme and anchors the bottom. If reskinning, change its fill to match the new theme's accent color.",
    "Looth logo is small (~128px) bottom-left, NOT in a corner panel — the green strip is its bed.",
    "Subject positioned bottom-right (left 610, top 0), NOT centered — rule-of-thirds power point; text staircase gets the left two-thirds, subject gets the right third and bleeds off the bottom.",
    "Name banner polygon fill is 'rgba(43,35,24,0)' (fully transparent) — the banner group still carries chevron shape metadata so it can be re-enabled later."
  ],
